                <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-8">
                    <h2>Bhagyashree Padalkar</h2>
                    <h3>Fedora</h3>
                    <p>Bhagyashree(or Bee) is a recent graduate of the Indian Institute of Technology, Guwahati, India.She currently works as a researcher in decision making at Max Planck Institute, Berlin. Her primary research interests lie in understanding human behavior in information-rich online social environments. Her research draws heavily from Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing techniques. At Fedora, she works closely with the Community Operations team mostly contributing on metrics-related tasks. She is also a Google Summer of Code 2016 Mentor for Fedora, actively involved with the Fedora Women, Diversity Team and is a Marathi translator for Fedora. She also helped organize the 2015 Nov/Dec Fedora Election Cycle and is working towards being a Fedora Ambassador. She goes by bee2502 in IRC.</p>
